                        <origDate notBefore="1800" notAfter="1850" evidence="context">
                           The fragment referred to as <ref target="#p1"/> originates from a different manuscript, most likely dating to the first half of the 19th century, owing to the scribe 
                           <persName role="scribe" ref="PRS11077Zadengel">Zadǝngǝl</persName>, who is know from other dated manuscripts, such as <ref type="mss" corresp="ESagm001"/>. 
                           <ref target="#p1"/> has been inserted into the centrefold of <ref target="#q1"/>. It is difficult to determine whether the insertion took place while the manuscript was being produced or when it was repaired. 
                           </origDate>
                     </origin>
                     <provenance><persName role="scribe" ref="PRS11077Zadengel">Zadǝngǝl</persName>, most likely the scribe, is mentioned in the supplication formula on <locus target="#3vb"/>.</provenance>
